{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":533,"text":"Five years ago, I was on a sabbatical,"},{"time":3089,"text":"and I returned to the medical university"},{"time":5481,"text":"where I studied."},{"time":7343,"text":"I saw real patients and I wore the white coat"},{"time":12098,"text":"for the first time in 17 years,"},{"time":14907,"text":"in fact since I became a management consultant."}]},{"cues":[{"time":18384,"text":"There were two things that surprised me"},{"time":20308,"text":"during the month I spent."},{"time":22425,"text":"The first one was that the common theme"},{"time":24315,"text":"of the discussions we had were hospital budgets"},{"time":27823,"text":"and cost-cutting,"},{"time":29746,"text":"and the second thing, which really bothered me,"},{"time":31570,"text":"actually, was that several of the colleagues I met,"},{"time":34439,"text":"former friends from medical school,"},{"time":36500,"text":"who I knew to be some of the smartest,"},{"time":38637,"text":"most motivated, engaged and passionate people"},{"time":41606,"text":"I'd ever met,"},{"time":43160,"text":"many of them had turned cynical, disengaged,"},{"time":47091,"text":"or had distanced themselves\nfrom hospital management."},{"time":50598,"text":"So with this focus on cost-cutting,"},{"time":53372,"text":"I asked myself, are we forgetting the patient?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":57668,"text":"Many countries that you represent"},{"time":59672,"text":"and where I come from"},{"time":61269,"text":"struggle with the cost of healthcare."},{"time":64175,"text":"It's a big part of the national budgets."},{"time":67143,"text":"And many different reforms aim\nat holding back this growth."},{"time":70928,"text":"In some countries, we have long waiting times"},{"time":72945,"text":"for patients for surgery."},{"time":75152,"text":"In other countries, new drugs\nare not being reimbursed,"},{"time":77670,"text":"and therefore don't reach patients."},{"time":80642,"text":"In several countries, doctors and nurses"},{"time":82899,"text":"are the targets, to some extent, for the governments."},{"time":86956,"text":"After all, the costly decisions in health care"},{"time":90523,"text":"are taken by doctors and nurses."},{"time":92991,"text":"You choose an expensive lab test,"},{"time":95531,"text":"you choose to operate on an old and frail patient."},{"time":99158,"text":"So, by limiting the degrees of freedom of physicians,"},{"time":103632,"text":"this is a way to hold costs down."},{"time":106863,"text":"And ultimately, some physicians will say today"},{"time":109135,"text":"that they don't have the full liberty"},{"time":111802,"text":"to make the choices they think\nare right for their patients."},{"time":115322,"text":"So no wonder that some of my old colleagues"},{"time":117692,"text":"are frustrated."}]},{"cues":[{"time":120058,"text":"At BCG, we looked at this,"},{"time":122509,"text":"and we asked ourselves,"},{"time":124340,"text":"this can't be the right way of managing healthcare."},{"time":127852,"text":"And so we took a step back and we said,"},{"time":131072,"text":"\"What is it that we are trying to achieve?\""},{"time":133744,"text":"Ultimately, in the healthcare system,"},{"time":135975,"text":"we're aiming at improving health for the patients,"},{"time":139936,"text":"and we need to do so at a limited,"},{"time":142213,"text":"or affordable, cost."},{"time":144070,"text":"We call this value-based healthcare."},{"time":146793,"text":"On the screen behind me, you see what we mean"},{"time":148477,"text":"by value:"},{"time":150286,"text":"outcomes that matter to patients"},{"time":152772,"text":"relative to the money we spend."},{"time":155781,"text":"This was described beautifully in a book in 2006"},{"time":158526,"text":"by Michael Porter and Elizabeth Teisberg."}]},{"cues":[{"time":162531,"text":"On this picture, you have my father-in-law"},{"time":165674,"text":"surrounded by his three beautiful daughters."},{"time":169060,"text":"When we started doing our research at BCG,"},{"time":172096,"text":"we decided not to look so much at the costs,"},{"time":174756,"text":"but to look at the quality instead,"},{"time":177296,"text":"and in the research, one of the things"},{"time":179877,"text":"that fascinated us was the variation we saw."},{"time":182919,"text":"You compare hospitals in a country,"},{"time":185292,"text":"you'll find some that are extremely good,"},{"time":187508,"text":"but you'll find a large number\nthat are vastly much worse."},{"time":190953,"text":"The differences were dramatic."},{"time":193115,"text":"Erik, my father-in-law,"},{"time":195177,"text":"he suffers from prostate cancer,"},{"time":197708,"text":"and he probably needs surgery."},{"time":200018,"text":"Now living in Europe, he can\nchoose to go to Germany"},{"time":202725,"text":"that has a well-reputed healthcare system."},{"time":206437,"text":"If he goes there and goes to the average hospital,"},{"time":210137,"text":"he will have the risk of becoming incontinent"},{"time":214211,"text":"by about 50 percent,"},{"time":216185,"text":"so he would have to start wearing diapers again."},{"time":219158,"text":"You flip a coin. Fifty percent risk. That's quite a lot."},{"time":223095,"text":"If he instead would go to Hamburg,"},{"time":225997,"text":"and to a clinic called the Martini-Klinik,"},{"time":228508,"text":"the risk would be only one in 20."},{"time":231191,"text":"Either you a flip a coin,"},{"time":232776,"text":"or you have a one in 20 risk."},{"time":234809,"text":"That's a huge difference, a seven-fold difference."},{"time":238314,"text":"When we look at many hospitals"},{"time":240299,"text":"for many different diseases,"},{"time":241973,"text":"we see these huge differences."}]},{"cues":[{"time":244990,"text":"But you and I don't know. We don't have the data."},{"time":247884,"text":"And often, the data actually doesn't exist."},{"time":249731,"text":"Nobody knows."},{"time":251450,"text":"So going the hospital is a lottery."}]},{"cues":[{"time":255803,"text":"Now, it doesn't have to be that way. There is hope."},{"time":260083,"text":"In the late '70s, there were a group"},{"time":262575,"text":"of Swedish orthopedic surgeons"},{"time":265007,"text":"who met at their annual meeting,"},{"time":266866,"text":"and they were discussing the different procedures"},{"time":268827,"text":"they used to operate hip surgery."},{"time":272131,"text":"To the left of this slide, you see a variety"},{"time":273859,"text":"of metal pieces, artificial hips that you would use"},{"time":276896,"text":"for somebody who needs a new hip."},{"time":279755,"text":"They all realized they had\ntheir individual way of operating."},{"time":283004,"text":"They all argued that, \"My technique is the best,\""},{"time":285401,"text":"but none of them actually knew,\nand they admitted that."},{"time":288274,"text":"So they said, \"We probably need to measure quality"},{"time":292223,"text":"so we know and can learn from what's best.\""},{"time":296392,"text":"So they in fact spent two years debating,"},{"time":299591,"text":"\"So what is quality in hip surgery?\""},{"time":301886,"text":"\"Oh, we should measure this.\"\n\"No, we should measure that.\""},{"time":304260,"text":"And they finally agreed."},{"time":306311,"text":"And once they had agreed, they started measuring,"},{"time":308962,"text":"and started sharing the data."},{"time":311365,"text":"Very quickly, they found that if you put cement"},{"time":313964,"text":"in the bone of the patient"},{"time":315470,"text":"before you put the metal shaft in,"},{"time":317648,"text":"it actually lasted a lot longer,"},{"time":319784,"text":"and most patients would never have to be"},{"time":321542,"text":"re-operated on in their lifetime."},{"time":323903,"text":"They published the data,"},{"time":325571,"text":"and it actually transformed\nclinical practice in the country."},{"time":328694,"text":"Everybody saw this makes a lot of sense."},{"time":331985,"text":"Since then, they publish every year."},{"time":334022,"text":"Once a year, they publish the league table:"},{"time":335970,"text":"who's best, who's at the bottom?"},{"time":338457,"text":"And they visit each other to try to learn,"},{"time":341137,"text":"so a continuous cycle of improvement."},{"time":344927,"text":"For many years, Swedish hip surgeons"},{"time":347734,"text":"had the best results in the world,"},{"time":350121,"text":"at least for those who actually were measuring,"},{"time":352599,"text":"and many were not."}]},{"cues":[{"time":355035,"text":"Now I found this principle really exciting."},{"time":357917,"text":"So the physicians get together,"},{"time":359720,"text":"they agree on what quality is,"},{"time":361845,"text":"they start measuring, they share the data,"},{"time":365559,"text":"they find who's best, and they learn from it."},{"time":369075,"text":"Continuous improvement."}]},{"cues":[{"time":371667,"text":"Now, that's not the only exciting part."},{"time":374215,"text":"That's exciting in itself."},{"time":376466,"text":"But if you bring back the cost side of the equation,"},{"time":379417,"text":"and look at that,"},{"time":380877,"text":"it turns out, those who have focused on quality,"},{"time":383882,"text":"they actually also have the lowest costs,"},{"time":385915,"text":"although that's not been the purpose\nin the first place."},{"time":388584,"text":"So if you look at the hip surgery story again,"},{"time":391614,"text":"there was a study done a couple years ago"},{"time":393985,"text":"where they compared the U.S. and Sweden."},{"time":397983,"text":"They looked at how many patients have needed"},{"time":399908,"text":"to be re-operated on seven years after the first surgery."},{"time":403989,"text":"In the United States, the number was three times"},{"time":406876,"text":"higher than in Sweden."},{"time":409064,"text":"So many unnecessary surgeries,"},{"time":412504,"text":"and so much unnecessary suffering"},{"time":415244,"text":"for all the patients who were operated on"},{"time":416936,"text":"in that seven year period."},{"time":419403,"text":"Now, you can imagine how much savings"},{"time":420982,"text":"there would be for society."}]},{"cues":[{"time":423482,"text":"We did a study where we looked at OECD data."},{"time":426653,"text":"OECD does, every so often,"},{"time":429503,"text":"look at quality of care"},{"time":431659,"text":"where they can find the data\nacross the member countries."},{"time":436184,"text":"The United States has, for many diseases,"},{"time":438786,"text":"actually a quality which is below the average"},{"time":440990,"text":"in OECD."},{"time":442408,"text":"Now, if the American healthcare system"},{"time":444562,"text":"would focus a lot more on measuring quality,"},{"time":446998,"text":"and raise quality just to the level of average OECD,"},{"time":451047,"text":"it would save the American people"},{"time":453385,"text":"500 billion U.S. dollars a year."},{"time":457511,"text":"That's 20 percent of the budget,"},{"time":460738,"text":"of the healthcare budget of the country."}]},{"cues":[{"time":463451,"text":"Now you may say that these numbers"},{"time":465558,"text":"are fantastic, and it's all logical,"},{"time":468449,"text":"but is it possible?"},{"time":470459,"text":"This would be a paradigm shift in healthcare,"},{"time":473098,"text":"and I would argue that not only can it be done,"},{"time":476678,"text":"but it has to be done."},{"time":478912,"text":"The agents of change are the doctors and nurses"},{"time":482303,"text":"in the healthcare system."}]},{"cues":[{"time":484995,"text":"In my practice as a consultant,"},{"time":487109,"text":"I meet probably a hundred or more than a hundred"},{"time":489376,"text":"doctors and nurses and other hospital"},{"time":492253,"text":"or healthcare staff every year."},{"time":495210,"text":"The one thing they have in common is"},{"time":497396,"text":"they really care about what they achieve"},{"time":499674,"text":"in terms of quality for their patients."},{"time":502908,"text":"Physicians are, like most of you in the audience,"},{"time":504991,"text":"very competitive."},{"time":507527,"text":"They were always best in class."},{"time":509277,"text":"We were always best in class."},{"time":512775,"text":"And if somebody can show them that the result"},{"time":515389,"text":"they perform for their patients"},{"time":516976,"text":"is no better than what others do,"},{"time":519830,"text":"they will do whatever it takes to improve."},{"time":522537,"text":"But most of them don't know."},{"time":524870,"text":"But physicians have another characteristic."},{"time":527285,"text":"They actually thrive from peer recognition."},{"time":531127,"text":"If a cardiologist calls another cardiologist"},{"time":533361,"text":"in a competing hospital"},{"time":535209,"text":"and discusses why that other hospital"},{"time":537238,"text":"has so much better results, they will share."},{"time":540033,"text":"They will share the information on how to improve."},{"time":543750,"text":"So it is, by measuring and creating transparency,"},{"time":547870,"text":"you get a cycle of continuous improvement,"},{"time":550780,"text":"which is what this slide shows."}]},{"cues":[{"time":553654,"text":"Now, you may say this is a nice idea,"},{"time":556595,"text":"but this isn't only an idea."},{"time":558499,"text":"This is happening in reality."},{"time":560527,"text":"We're creating a global community,"},{"time":563681,"text":"and a large global community,"},{"time":565544,"text":"where we'll be able to measure and compare"},{"time":568091,"text":"what we achieve."},{"time":569805,"text":"Together with two academic institutions,"},{"time":572432,"text":"Michael Porter at Harvard Business School,"},{"time":574426,"text":"and the Karolinska Institute in Sweden,"},{"time":576310,"text":"BCG has formed something we call ICHOM."},{"time":580275,"text":"You may think that's a sneeze,"},{"time":582480,"text":"but it's not a sneeze, it's an acronym."},{"time":585607,"text":"It stands for the International Consortium"},{"time":588183,"text":"for Health Outcome Measurement."},{"time":591143,"text":"We're bringing together leading physicians"},{"time":593892,"text":"and patients to discuss, disease by disease,"},{"time":597483,"text":"what is really quality,"},{"time":599585,"text":"what should we measure,"},{"time":601572,"text":"and to make those standards global."},{"time":604060,"text":"They've worked -- four working groups have worked"},{"time":606415,"text":"during the past year:"},{"time":608383,"text":"cataracts, back pain,"},{"time":611227,"text":"coronary artery disease, which is,\nfor instance, heart attack,"},{"time":615453,"text":"and prostate cancer."},{"time":617634,"text":"The four groups will publish their data"},{"time":620038,"text":"in November of this year."},{"time":621880,"text":"That's the first time we'll be comparing"},{"time":624338,"text":"apples to apples, not only within a country,"},{"time":627284,"text":"but between countries."},{"time":630465,"text":"Next year, we're planning to do eight diseases,"},{"time":634443,"text":"the year after, 16."},{"time":636997,"text":"In three years' time, we plan to have covered"},{"time":639453,"text":"40 percent of the disease burden."},{"time":642566,"text":"Compare apples to apples. Who's better?"},{"time":645216,"text":"Why is that?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":648267,"text":"Five months ago,"},{"time":651132,"text":"I led a workshop at the largest university hospital"},{"time":654166,"text":"in Northern Europe."},{"time":655876,"text":"They have a new CEO, and she has a vision:"},{"time":659363,"text":"I want to manage my big institution much more"},{"time":662969,"text":"on quality, outcomes that matter to patients."},{"time":667074,"text":"This particular day, we sat in a workshop"},{"time":670572,"text":"together with physicians, nurses and other staff,"},{"time":673382,"text":"discussing leukemia in children."},{"time":677880,"text":"The group discussed,"},{"time":679657,"text":"how do we measure quality today?"},{"time":681697,"text":"Can we measure it better than we do?"},{"time":684262,"text":"We discussed, how do we treat these kids,"},{"time":686484,"text":"what are important improvements?"},{"time":688535,"text":"And we discussed what are\nthe costs for these patients,"},{"time":691316,"text":"can we do treatment more efficiently?"},{"time":693664,"text":"There was an enormous energy in the room."},{"time":695608,"text":"There were so many ideas, so much enthusiasm."},{"time":699097,"text":"At the end of the meeting,"},{"time":701391,"text":"the chairman of the department, he stood up."},{"time":704700,"text":"He looked over the group and he said --"},{"time":709277,"text":"first he raised his hand, I forgot that --"},{"time":711062,"text":"he raised his hand, clenched his fist,"},{"time":713531,"text":"and then he said to the group, \"Thank you."},{"time":716428,"text":"Thank you. Today, we're finally discussing"},{"time":719351,"text":"what this hospital does the right way.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":722925,"text":"By measuring value in healthcare,"},{"time":725012,"text":"that is not only costs"},{"time":727037,"text":"but outcomes that matter to patients,"},{"time":729510,"text":"we will make staff in hospitals"},{"time":731308,"text":"and elsewhere in the healthcare system"},{"time":733167,"text":"not a problem but an important part of the solution."},{"time":737261,"text":"I believe measuring value in healthcare"},{"time":739197,"text":"will bring about a revolution,"},{"time":741968,"text":"and I'm convinced that the founder"},{"time":744077,"text":"of modern medicine, the Greek Hippocrates,"},{"time":747540,"text":"who always put the patient at the center,"},{"time":750490,"text":"he would smile in his grave."}]},{"cues":[{"time":752652,"text":"Thank you."}]},{"cues":[{"time":755453,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}